### Next.js
- Use the App Router for better performance and organization.
- Implement proper error boundaries to handle errors gracefully.
- Utilize static site generation (SSG) and server-side rendering (SSR) appropriately for optimal performance.

### TypeScript
- Enable strict mode for better type safety and error detection.
- Prefer using interfaces over type aliases for defining object shapes.
- Utilize type guards and assertions to ensure type safety in complex scenarios.

### Testing: Jest
- Write unit tests for components and utility functions to ensure reliability.
- Use snapshot testing for React components to catch unexpected changes.
- Implement integration tests to verify the interaction between components and APIs.

### UI: Radix UI, Tailwind CSS, Lucide React, Shadcn
- Use Tailwind CSS for utility-first styling and maintain consistency across components.
- Follow Radix UI guidelines for accessible and customizable components.
- Ensure all UI components are responsive and adhere to accessibility standards.
- Utilize Lucide React icons for a consistent iconography across the application.

### Other: Firebase Auth, Zustand
- Implement Firebase Auth for secure user authentication and manage user sessions effectively.
- Use Zustand for state management to keep your application state predictable and easy to debug.